# Create a program using maths and f-Strings that tells us how
# many days, weeks, months we have left if we live until 90 years # old.
age = input("What is your current age?")

# Create variables to convert to int
years = 90 - int(age)
months = (90 * 12) - (int(age) * 12)
weeks = (90 * 52) - (int(age) * 52)
days = (90 * 365) - (int(age) * 365)

#Print using f-string to display data types during the string
print(f"You have {days} days, {weeks} weeks, and {months} months left.")
